{{Nihongo|'''''Ero kawaii'''''|エロ可愛い||literally "erotic cute"}}, or '''''erokawa''''', is a Japanese subculture that draws on Western notions of sexiness, in contrast to the popular [[Kawaii|cuteness]] (kawaii) trend. The term, coined in 2005, is a fusion of ''ero'' (shortened from the English word "erotic", which has negative connotations in Japanese culture) and the lighter ''[[kawaii]]'', meaning "cute".<ref name=buzz>{{Citation | title = Buzzword: ero-kakkoii | date = 2006-02-22 | url = http://web-jpn.org/trends/buzz/bz0602.html | accessdate = 2009-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uniorb.com/ATREND/Japanwatch/eroticcool.htm|title="Erotic-Cool" Culture in Japan|date=2007-08-08|last=Lee|first=Diana|work=Uniorb.com}}</ref>

==History==
''Ero kawaii'' started with singer [[Kumi Koda]] using the term to describe her own style.<ref name=buzz/>

