[[Image:Mcconnell center.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the McConnell center]] The '''McConnell Center''' is an endowed institution created in 1991 by [[United States Senate|U.S. Senator]] [[Mitch McConnell]], and the [[University of Louisville]].
The McConnell Center's mission includes four major components: * The McConnell Scholars Program *Public Lecture Series *Civic Education Program *U.S. Senator Mitch McConnell and Secretary Elaine L. Chao Archives
The core of the McConnell Center is the McConnell Scholarship, offered each year to ten high school seniors from the Commonwealth of [[Kentucky]]. These students, selected based upon their high school achievement, are offered tuition scholarships to the University of Louisville, as well as opportunities for travel, internships, meeting with influential policy makers and the opportunity to study abroad in [[China]].
Recently, the scholars in the McConnell Center have met with [[President of the United States|President]] [[George W. Bush]], [[United States Chief Justice]] [[John Roberts]],<ref>[http://www.courier-journal.com/article/20090419/NEWS01/904190397/Chief+Justice+John+Roberts+speaks+at+U+of+L]{{dead link|date=March 2011}}</ref> Senator [[Ted Kennedy|Edward Kennedy]],<ref>[http://php.louisville.edu/news/news.php?news=497 Ted Kennedy to speak in McConnell Center event > News > University of Louisville: It's Happening Here<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Senator [[Harry Reid]],<ref>[http://php.louisville.edu/news/news.php?news=999 U.S. Senate majority leader to address bipartisanship in talk Oct. 15 > News > University of Louisville: It's Happening Here<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Senator [[Richard Lugar]],<ref>[https://php.louisville.edu/news/news.php?news=433#lugar This Week at U of L (Sept. 13–19) > News > University of Louisville: It's Happening Here<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[United States Secretary of State]] [[Condoleezza Rice]],<ref>[http://php.louisville.edu/news/news.php?news=170 Rice visits U of L as guest of McConnell Center > News > University of Louisville: It's Happening Here<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[United States Secretary of Labor|Secretary of Labor]] [[Elaine Chao]] (Senator McConnell's wife) and [[Lynne Cheney]].<ref>[http://php.louisville.edu/advancement/ocm/news/release.php?relid=701 University of Louisville :: News Releases :: LYNNE CHENEY, MCCONNELL CENTER CELEBRATE CONSTITUTION DAY 2006<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The McConnell Center has also started a civics learning program to encourage classrooms in Kentucky to teach students history and the virtues of citizenship.
The Chair of the McConnell Center is Dr. [[Gary L. Gregg]] II and alumni include [[J. Scott Jennings]]. The Center's non-resident fellows include Dr. [[Barbara A. Perry]].
